headline: Dollar General: JPM lifts stock on sales momentum, management ‘back on offense’
summary: Investing.com -- Dollar General shares opened higher on Monday after JPMorgan upgraded the discount retailer to Overweight, citing improving sales trends, margin expansion and upside to earnings estimates following a recent management roadshow.
